Issues to be urgently addressed include:
* The high rate of preventable deaths and illnesses due to water-borne diseases;
* Contamination of fresh groundwater sources by human settlements and sanitation;
* Impacts of climate variability and change on the availability of fresh water;
* Difficulties in protecting, conserving and managing freshwater sources;
* Growth in demand for water especially in urban areas;
* Inequities in provision of services to schools, hospitals, clinics, rural, outer island and urban communities;

Issues to be urgently addressed include:
* The high rate of preventable deaths and illnesses due to water-borne diseases;
